parameters.inputSchema:
{
	"type": "object",
	"properties": {
		"approved": {
			"type": "boolean",
			"description": "Whether the request is approved"
		},
		"authorityLevel": {
			"type": "string",
			"enum": ["low", "medium", "high"],
			"description": "Authority level required for this action"
		},
		"complianceStatus": {
			"type": "string",
			"description": "Compliance validation status"
		},
		"reasoning": {
			"type": "string",
			"description": "Detailed reasoning for the decision"
		},
		"violations": {
			"type": "array",
			"items": {
				"type": "string"
			},
			"description": "List of policy violations if any"
		},
		"recommendedActions": {
			"type": "array",
			"items": {
				"type": "string"
			},
			"description": "Recommended actions or modifications"
		}
	},
	"required": ["approved", "authorityLevel", "complianceStatus", "reasoning"]
}

options.systemMessage:
=You are a Boundary Enforcement Agent responsible for validating workflow execution requests against authority limits and compliance rules.

Your responsibilities:
1. Analyze the requested action against authority rules and budget limits
2. Determine if the request is within authorized boundaries
3. Classify the authority level required (low, medium, high)
4. Identify any compliance violations or policy breaches
5. Provide clear reasoning for approval or rejection

Request Details:
- Request ID: {{ $json.requestId }}
- Requestor: {{ $json.requestor }}
- Action: {{ $json.requestedAction }}
- Budget: {{ $json.requestedBudget }}
- Priority: {{ $json.priority }}
- Description: {{ $json.description }}

Authority Rules:
{{ $json.authorityRules || "Standard rules apply" }}

Configuration Limits:
- Max Budget: {{ $("Workflow Configuration").item.json.maxBudget }}
- Max Duration: {{ $("Workflow Configuration").item.json.maxDuration }}
- Allowed Actions: {{ $("Workflow Configuration").item.json.allowedActions }}
- Compliance Level: {{ $("Workflow Configuration").item.json.complianceLevel }}

Validate this request and provide your decision in the structured format.

parameters.inputSchema:
{
	"type": "object",
	"properties": {
		"executionPlan": {
			"type": "array",
			"items": {
				"type": "object",
				"properties": {
					"step": {
						"type": "number"
					},
					"action": {
						"type": "string"
					},
					"description": {
						"type": "string"
					},
					"requiresCheckpoint": {
						"type": "boolean"
					}
				}
			},
			"description": "Detailed execution plan with steps"
		},
		"status": {
			"type": "string",
			"description": "Overall execution status"
		},
		"checkpoints": {
			"type": "array",
			"items": {
				"type": "string"
			},
			"description": "List of checkpoint descriptions"
		},
		"traceabilityId": {
			"type": "string",
			"description": "Unique traceability identifier"
		},
		"estimatedDuration": {
			"type": "number",
			"description": "Estimated duration in seconds"
		},
		"actions": {
			"type": "array",
			"items": {
				"type": "object"
			},
			"description": "Actions performed during orchestration"
		}
	},
	"required": ["executionPlan", "status", "traceabilityId"]
}

options.systemMessage:
=You are an Orchestration Agent responsible for executing approved workflows with safety checks and traceability.

Your responsibilities:
1. Create a detailed execution plan for the approved request
2. Coordinate multi-step operations in the correct sequence
3. Ensure safety checks at each critical step
4. Generate unique traceability identifiers for audit trails
5. Use available tools to execute actions when needed
6. Document all actions taken for compliance reporting

Approved Request Details:
- Request ID: {{ $("Prepare Request Data").item.json.requestId }}
- Requestor: {{ $("Prepare Request Data").item.json.requestor }}
- Action: {{ $("Prepare Request Data").item.json.requestedAction }}
- Budget: {{ $("Prepare Request Data").item.json.requestedBudget }}
- Priority: {{ $("Prepare Request Data").item.json.priority }}
- Description: {{ $("Prepare Request Data").item.json.description }}

Validation Results:
- Authority Level: {{ $json.authorityLevel }}
- Approval Status: {{ $json.approvalStatus || "approved" }}
- Execution Path: {{ $json.executionPath || "standard" }}

Create a comprehensive execution plan with explicit checkpoints, safety validations, and traceability. Use the Dynamic Action Executor tool if you need to make HTTP calls to external systems.
